The Challenge
Legal departments are under growing scrutiny to run efficiently and effectively – like well-oiled machines. Data is the foundation for assessing the health of the organization, influencing change and advocating for growth. Do you like telling stories with data? Do you find yourself looking at data trends for new ways to drive efficiency? Do you like working on puzzles and using technology, such as PowerBI, to solve problems and improve productivity? Does the cross-section of technology and data excite you?
If these sorts of questions intrigue you, come join the Adobe Legal and Government Relations (LGR) team! Adobe’s Legal Operations team is looking to add an Operations Data Analyst to the team. This role will be located at Adobe’s headquarters in San Jose, California, and will be responsible for all things data – gathering, reviewing, assessing, analyzing, reporting, and influencing behavioral changes as a result.
Specifically, this Operations Data Analyst will support Adobe LGR by creating data-driven reports and providing analytical insights that illuminate how the department is running its business. This includes working closely with key internal legal stakeholders, from Compliance to Operations to HR, to understand their business. You will function as the coordinator and internal point of contact regarding needs and requirements for Legal data, metrics and reporting.
You will utilize and analyze multiple data sources, and will build clear visualizations that provide actionable insights that assist the department in accomplishing its goals. Following your analysis, you will generate and disseminate reports to key stakeholders, which will include oral presentations to senior leaders. This includes determining the effectiveness of current operational activities, identifying problems and areas for opportunity, and partnering to develop solutions.
Key areas of responsibility include refining and creating legal spend reports (including reports that compile total spend and savings from AFAs, diversity-related spend, internal/external spend, etc.)and department-wide dashboards, including litigation metrics, operational metrics such as website analysis and resource analysis, key contract metrics, etc. You will serve as a liaison to lawyers and other legal professionals, as well as other cross-functional teams.
An adaptive and fast learner, you will continuously gain a deeper understanding of the department’s data and report on key metrics in order to meet business needs. You are also able to identify and interpret trends and patterns in data sets to tease out potential areas of influence or change.
